translations: v.（在日期上）早于，先于……发生（或出现）（predate 的过去式和过去分词）

sentences.translation: 他的麻烦早在经济衰退前就出现了。

sentences.sentence: I think so-that undergraduate major in philosophy predated law school after all.
sentences.translation: 我是这样想的——本科时的哲学专业毕竟比法学院的学习在先。

sentences.sentence: It was impossible to say whether their current heart damage predated their marathon training.
sentences.translation: 因此，无法断定他们心脏受损是发生在马拉松训练之前或者之后。
